cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with backpropagation through neural networks for natural language processing tasks, specifically those involving structured predictions such as parsing and sentiment classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a new optimization technique, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments involve NLP pipelines, which could also relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the pipelines involve image processing. Finally, the paper deals with neural networks, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
